Tony Okafor, Awka A former Governor of Anambra State, Chief Chukwuemeka Ezeife, has met with some Peoples Democratic Party aspirants for the 2021 Anambra State governorship election. The aspirants who hail from Anambra South Senatorial District, agreed that the position be zoned to their district. This was contained in a communique issued after the meeting. A former president of Transnational Corporation of Nigeria, Valentine Ozoigbo, who is also an aspirant, told our correspondent over the telephone on Tuesday, that the communique was “an authentic document.” The communique read in part, “We re-affirm that the next governor of Anambra State in the forthcoming gubernatorial election shall emerge from the Anambra South Senatorial District in line with the existing zoning arrangements in the State.” Signatories to the communique include Dr Chukwuemeka Ezeife, Linus Ukachukwu, Senator Uche Ekwunife, Chris Azubuogu, Chuma Nzeribe, Ugochukwu Okeke, Emeka Etiaba (SAN), Obunike Ohaegbu (Ezesinachi), Dr. Ifedi Okwenna, Valentine Ozigbo and Godwin Ezeemo. Copyright PUNCH.
